## Built-binary manual walk-through

Binary built with `go build -o /tmp/etude-nudge ./cmd/etude`.

| step | observed |
|---|---|
| Fresh init, no nudge config, `run list` | no stderr line — baseline preserved. |
| `retro nudge status` with no config | JSON `{enabled:false, threshold:3, ..., would_emit:false}` — exact AC#6 keys. |
| Enable nudge `threshold:2`, capture 2 runs, `run list` | stderr: `etude: retro nudge: 2 bead(s) since last retro (threshold 2); ...`. Stdout: clean run-list table. |
| `retro nudge status` while overdue | JSON `would_emit:true`. **Stderr empty** (`retro nudge` subtree silenced). |
| `retro nudge dismiss --for 1` | stdout: `snoozed retro nudge for 1 more bead(s); next reminder when runs-since-last-retro reaches 3`. Snooze file `.git/etude/retro-nudge-snooze.json` written with `runs_at_snooze=2, snooze_for=1, last_retro_id_at_snooze=""`. **Stderr empty** (dismiss invocation silenced). |
| `run list` while snoozed | stderr empty. |
| Capture 1 more run (`runs_since_last_retro=3`), `run list` | nudge re-fires. |
| Dismiss `--for 100`, capture a workflow-scope retro, then capture 2 more runs and `run list` | nudge fires — stale snooze invalidated by new retro id. |
| `etude --help` | stderr empty. |
| `etude --version` | stderr empty. |
| `etude completion bash` | stderr empty (completion script on stdout only). |
| `etude __complete ru ""` (indirectly tested in unit tests, same code path as above) | stderr empty. |

